The paper discusses the use of Reinforcement Learning (RL) and Imitation Learning (IL) in decision-making tasks with the assistance of a human teacher. This falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the challenges of dealing with large amounts of environment states and action spaces, which is related to Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of a human teacher in the learning process involves Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.RO, cs.HC, and cs.SY.
